<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	Empty entitlements file. With ENABLE_APP_SANDBOX: NO and
	ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME: YES (set in project.yml), the app runs
	unsandboxed but with hardened runtime. Most utility apps need
	nothing more.

	Add entitlements below as needed. Common ones:

	iCloud Key-Value Storage (small settings sync across Macs):
	<key>com.apple.developer.ubiquity-kvstore-identifier</key>
	<string>$(TeamIdentifierPrefix)$(CFBundleIdentifier)</string>

	JIT compilation (rare, breaks hardened runtime by default):
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
	<true/>

	Apple Events to other apps (e.g. controlling Music.app):
	<key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
	<true/>

	Loading unsigned/non-team libraries (use sparingly):
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
	<true/>

	When this file is renamed to {{APP_NAME_NOSPACE}}.entitlements
	in your project, the project.yml CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS setting
	will pick it up automatically.
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
